\begin_layout Section
Corporate Financial Accounting
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Financial accounting & reporting is concerned only with the information
 that is available & disclosed by a firm to persons 
\series bold
external
\series default
 to the company.
 We won't consider: management accounting, non-profit & government institutions,
 tax accounting.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are many standards & regulations for accounting.
 There are international & internal boards in the U.S.
 In every country there are local regulators whose goal is to prevent fraund
 and to ensure transparency (making sure no 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

inside trading
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 is done).
 Stock exchanges can be somewhat controlled by legislators, but mostly it
 is believed that the free market behaves the best.
 Sometimes there are market failures, in such case there is an intervention.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The manager is legally responsible for making the best effort to deliver
 accurate and true financial reports (he is not reponsible for the debt
 itself).
\end_layout

