\begin_layout Section
The Financial Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
An understanding of financial statements requires an understanding of the
 business activities: goals & strategies, financing & investments, operations.
 For example, if one discovers a future huge (unexpected) presonal income,
 what would his actions be? - There are a lot of preparations for starting
 a business.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Financing: Usually first VCs, only then banks (banks usually don't want
 to be the first ones who put money - except tech market today).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Investments: Hiring & training people, buying machines & equipment, etc.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Operations: only after the previous stages are done, operations can be started.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The goal of the financial statement is to tell this story.
 What is the company goal & strategy? It might not be (initially) to maximize
 profit - but maybe acquire some market share first.
 It defines how operations are conducted.
\end_layout

